Post issue to GitHub repository

Source: R/post.R
post_issue.Rd

Post issue to GitHub repository

post_issue(ref, title, ...)

Arguments

ref

Repository reference (list) created by tidytracker::create_repo_ref
title

Issue title (required)
...

Additional user-defined body parameters

Value

Content of POST request as list

See also

Other post: post_milestone

Other issues: get_issue_events, get_issues, parse_issue_events, parse_issues, report_progress, viz_gantt_closed_links, viz_gantt_closed, viz_taskboard_links, viz_taskboard, viz_waterfall_issues

Examples

# NOT RUN {
myrepo <- create_repo_ref('emilyriederer', 'myrepo')
post_issue(myrepo,
  title = 'this is my issue's title',
  body = 'this is my issue's body',
  labels = c('priority:high', 'bug'))
# }
# NOT RUN {
# can be used in conjunction with reprex pkg
# example assumes code for reprex is on clipboard
reprex::reprex(venue = "gh")
post_issue(myrepo,
            title = "something is broken",
            body = paste( clipr::read_clip(), collapse = "\n") )
# }
